Citing the coronavirus pandemic, which has altered socio-economic activities around the world and the need to mitigate its effect on businesses and taxpayers, the Lagos State Internal Revenue Service (LIRS) has extended the deadline for filing of annual returns for individual taxpayers including self-employed persons from April 1 to May 31, 2020. Statutorily, the filing of annual returns expires on the March 31st of every fiscal year, and attracts stiff penalties for defaulters, LIRS said in a statement issued yesterday by the head, Corporate Communications, Monsurat Amasa. She quoted the chairman of LIRS, Mr. Ayodele Subair, as saying that the extension of deadline was in response to appeals made by taxpayers as well as a policy shift by the agency to assuage the effect of COVID-19 on the taxpayers and residents of Lagos State. Amasa said: “We implore the taxpayers to access our eTax platform for all tax operations and administration matters, including filing of annual returns from the comfort of their homes and offices. They can do this, by simply logging on to the eTax platform via https://etax.lirs.net or calling our Customer Care Centre on 0700 CALL LIRS (070022555477).’’ She said that further updates on business operations and alternative payment platforms of the service can be obtained by visiting the LIRS website, (www.lirs.gov.ng), and its various social media handles. She  appealed to the residents of Lagos State to support the efforts of the Lagos State Government  by adhering strictly to the COVID-19 safety guidelines as issued by relevant health authorities.